Two hundred and seventy nine of the new patients were found in Nairobi County, which remained in the lead in terms of the number of infections recorded daily per county. The number of declared Covid-19 infections in Kenya on Tuesday rose by 400 to 107,729, Health minister Mutahi Kagwe announced in a statement, saying 5,189 samples had been tested within a day. 

The Cabinet Secretary said the country had tested at least 1,322,806 samples for the disease by March 5, since reporting its first case about a year ago. 



